<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p> <gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/>  his grandfather and M<gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="lost">and</supplied> Aur(elia) Komike (daughter of) Hermeios, his m<supplied reason="lost">other</supplied>  <gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/></p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>It is probable that the text is listing those who have been or will be buried in the sarcophagus, the first name to survive being that of the owner's grandfather, and since l .2 gives almost certainly the name of his mother, the intervening one was, no doubt, his father, who may well have been a Marcus Aurelius.</p>
</div>
